Before diving into topics, understand WHY functions matter so deeply in AI and ML work. Every single thing in ML is built on functions:
•A neural network is a composition of functions applied layer by layer
•A loss function is literally a function that measures prediction error
•Data preprocessing pipelines are functions applied in sequence
•Model training is an optimization loop — minimizing a function
•Every scikit-learn transformer, every PyTorch layer, every LangChain chain — all functions
 
Core Idea When you master Python functions deeply, you will understand what ML libraries are DOING underneath — not just how to call them. This is the difference between a user and an engineer.
